The paper deals with the computational power of probabilistic and quantum Turing machines, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The addition of quantum bits to the model suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of quantum computing (cs.QL). The use of logarithmic space and the recognition of languages suggest that the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and automata and formal languages (cs.LO). Finally, the mention of interactive proof systems suggests that the paper may also fall under the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT).
